title: New data for the production of radionuclides in thin lead target by 660 MeV protons

x4freetext: New data for the production of radionuclides in thin
lead target by 660 MeV protons

x4codes.shortRef: Conf: Conf.on Nucl.Data for Sci.and Techn., Trieste 1997, Vol.2, p.1525 (1997)

x4codes.hlp: Joint Institute for Nuclear Research (JINR), Dubna

x4freetext: The lead foil of 30 mm diam.,0.1 mm thickness,
0.703 g weight in stack with Al-foil of the same
diam. were used.
Collective and Microscopic Model Calculations.
The lead foil was irradiated with protons
during to 11 min. The proton flux was 1.8E+11 1/cm2/sec
34 Spectrum measurements from 10 to 60 min.
duration were made during the first 18 hours. The next
ones were carried out after day, 25 days and half of
year.
